Updated `content/papers/predictive.md` with minimal structural QA edits only.

Summary of changes:
- Added missing blank lines to enforce paragraph boundaries where prose paragraphs were unintentionally merged by single newlines.
- Split inline display-equation blocks onto proper standalone lines for cleaner Hugo+KaTeX markdown rendering (equation content/tags unchanged).
- Added missing blank lines between several adjacent bibliography entries in `## REFERENCES` so each citation renders as a distinct paragraph.
- Removed trailing unreferenced metadata-style footnote block (`[^1]: Visiting Fellow...`) at the end of the file.
- Kept equation numbering consistent: all in-text equation references still map to visible tagged display equations (`\tag{1}` through `\tag{20}`).
- No abstract duplication found in body; no figure-related edits made.
